
                                            The trio appeared in court on Friday after members acted on information about a possible human trafficking incident in Milnerton.
                                         CAPE TOWN - Three people have been arrested on human trafficking charges.  This follows an investigation by the Hawks on a woman who was allegedly lured to Cape Town from Johannesburg with promises of a job. She was then apparently held against her will and forced to become a prostitute.  The trio appeared in court on Friday after members acted on information about a possible human trafficking incident in Milnerton. A 26-year-old victim was allegedly lured to Cape Town from Johannesburg by a woman known to her, who had promised her a job. On her arrival, two men allegedly picked her up. She was then kept against her will and allegedly turned into a sex-worker.  The woman managed to escape and reported the matter to authorities.